{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012rYcn6ipoFsWK9D3hL5Pmo","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F28 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC.md §7.6 — Right Panel — Live Feed:\n6\t\n7\t- Connects to `GET /api/live` (SSE)\n8\t- Displays newest events at top (prepend, not append)\n9\t- Each event card shows:\n10\t  - Timestamp (relative: \"2s ago\")\n11\t  - Event name (colored chip by event type)\n12\t  - Resolved identity (device or user)\n13\t  - Properties (compact JSON)\n14\t- Max 200 events shown; older ones are discarded\n15\t- Connection status indicator: green dot \"Live\" / red dot \"Disconnected\"\n16\t- Clear button\n17\t- Pause/Resume toggle (pauses rendering, buffers in background)\n18\t\n19\t## Dependencies\n20\t\n21\tCompleted features this builds on:\n22\t- **F17** (`features/F17-done.md`) — `GET /api/live` SSE route\n23\t- **F27** (`features/F27-done.md`) — Testing page left panel with two-panel layout at `/test`\n24\t- **F21** (`features/F21-done.md`) — JsonChip and IdentityChip shared UI components\n25\t\n26\tExact file paths that will be imported or extended:\n27\t- `src/app/test/page.tsx` — existing two-panel layout with placeholder right panel\n28\t- `src/app/api/live/route.ts` — SSE endpoint (consumed, not modified)\n29\t- `src/lib/live.ts` — `EventRow` type re-exported from identity\n30\t- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `EventRow` type\n31\t- `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx` — for compact JSON property display\n32\t- `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` — for resolved identity display\n33\t\n34\t## Files to create or modify\n35\t\n36\t- CREATE `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts` — custom hook: SSE connection, event buffering, pause/resume, max 200 cap\n37\t- CREATE `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx` — right panel component rendering the live feed\n38\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts` — unit tests for the hook\n39\t- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx` — unit tests for the component\n40\t- MODIFY `src/app/test/page.tsx` — replace placeholder right panel with `<LiveFeed />`\n41\t\n42\t## Implementation order\n43\t\n44\t1. **Create `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts`** — custom hook that:\n45\t   - Opens an `EventSource` to `/api/live` on mount\n46\t   - Parses incoming SSE `data:` messages as `EventRow` objects\n47\t   - Maintains an event list state (newest first, prepend), capped at 200\n48\t   - Exposes `paused` state + `togglePause()` — when paused, incoming events are buffered in a ref; on resume, buffered events are flushed to state\n49\t   - Exposes `connectionStatus: \"live\" | \"disconnected\"` derived from `EventSource.readyState` and `onopen`/`onerror` handlers\n50\t   - Exposes `clearEvents()` to empty the list\n51\t   - Closes `EventSource` on unmount\n52\t\n53\t2. **Create `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx`** — React client component that:\n54\t   - Calls `useLiveFeed()`\n55\t   - Renders connection status indicator (green/red dot + text)\n56\t   - Renders Pause/Resume toggle button and Clear button in a toolbar\n57\t   - Renders each event as a card/list item with: relative timestamp, event name colored chip, resolved identity (IdentityChip), properties (JsonChip)\n58\t   - Handles empty state (\"No events yet\")\n59\t\n60\t3. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts`** — unit tests for the hook\n61\t\n62\t4. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx`** — unit tests for the component\n63\t\n64\t5. **Modify `src/app/test/page.tsx`** — import `LiveFeed` and replace the placeholder `<Paper>` content in the right panel\n65\t\n66\t## Sprint contract\n67\t\n68\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n69\t- [ ] Linter → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n70\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n71\t- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n72\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts` exists and exports `useLiveFeed`\n73\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx` exists and exports `LiveFeed`\n74\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts` exists\n75\t- [ ] File `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx` exists\n76\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Live` (connection status text)\n77\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Pause` (pause/resume button)\n78\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Clear` (clear button)\n79\t\n80\t## Test plan\n81\t\n82\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts`\n83\t- **Module under test**: `useLiveFeed` from `@/components/test/useLiveFeed`\n84\t- **Cases to cover**:\n85\t  - Initial state: events array is empty, status is `\"disconnected\"`, paused is `false`\n86\t  - Receiving SSE messages prepends events to the list (newest first)\n87\t  - Events list is capped at 200; when a 201st event arrives the oldest is dropped\n88\t  - `togglePause()` sets paused to `true`; incoming events during pause are buffered\n89\t  - Resuming (calling `togglePause()` again) flushes buffered events into state\n90\t  - `clearEvents()` resets the events array to empty\n91\t  - Connection status transitions to `\"live\"` when EventSource opens\n92\t  - Connection status transitions to `\"disconnected\"` when EventSource fires error\n93\t  - EventSource is closed on unmount (cleanup)\n94\t\n95\t- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx`\n96\t- **Module under test**: `LiveFeed` from `@/components/test/LiveFeed`\n97\t- **Cases to cover**:\n98\t  - Renders connection status indicator with text \"Live\" or \"Disconnected\"\n99\t  - Renders Pause and Clear buttons\n100\t  - Shows empty state text when no events\n101\t  - Renders event cards with event name, relative timestamp, resolved identity, and properties when events exist\n102\t  - Clicking Pause toggles to Resume label\n103\t  - Clicking Clear empties the event list\n104\t\n105\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n106\t\n107\t## Risks and open questions\n108\t\n109\tNone. The SSE endpoint (`GET /api/live`) is already implemented in F17. The spec is clear on all UI behaviors. Relative timestamps (e.g., \"2s ago\") will be computed client-side; no external dependency is needed — a simple `formatRelativeTime` helper suffices.\n110\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"496fb2ae-93e4-48b2-b968-7ed4da55eb0e","uuid":"f8d097cc-4eee-426d-a9e4-cbb404af2d6f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:03:07.007Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F28-plan.md","content":"# F28 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC.md §7.6 — Right Panel — Live Feed:\n\n- Connects to `GET /api/live` (SSE)\n- Displays newest events at top (prepend, not append)\n- Each event card shows:\n  - Timestamp (relative: \"2s ago\")\n  - Event name (colored chip by event type)\n  - Resolved identity (device or user)\n  - Properties (compact JSON)\n- Max 200 events shown; older ones are discarded\n- Connection status indicator: green dot \"Live\" / red dot \"Disconnected\"\n- Clear button\n- Pause/Resume toggle (pauses rendering, buffers in background)\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n- **F17** (`features/F17-done.md`) — `GET /api/live` SSE route\n- **F27** (`features/F27-done.md`) — Testing page left panel with two-panel layout at `/test`\n- **F21** (`features/F21-done.md`) — JsonChip and IdentityChip shared UI components\n\nExact file paths that will be imported or extended:\n- `src/app/test/page.tsx` — existing two-panel layout with placeholder right panel\n- `src/app/api/live/route.ts` — SSE endpoint (consumed, not modified)\n- `src/lib/live.ts` — `EventRow` type re-exported from identity\n- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `EventRow` type\n- `src/components/ui/JsonChip.tsx` — for compact JSON property display\n- `src/components/ui/IdentityChip.tsx` — for resolved identity display\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts` — custom hook: SSE connection, event buffering, pause/resume, max 200 cap\n- CREATE `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx` — right panel component rendering the live feed\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts` — unit tests for the hook\n- CREATE `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx` — unit tests for the component\n- MODIFY `src/app/test/page.tsx` — replace placeholder right panel with `<LiveFeed />`\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts`** — custom hook that:\n   - Opens an `EventSource` to `/api/live` on mount\n   - Parses incoming SSE `data:` messages as `EventRow` objects\n   - Maintains an event list state (newest first, prepend), capped at 200\n   - Exposes `paused` state + `togglePause()` — when paused, incoming events are buffered in a ref; on resume, buffered events are flushed to state\n   - Exposes `connectionStatus: \"live\" | \"disconnected\"` derived from `EventSource.readyState` and `onopen`/`onerror` handlers\n   - Exposes `clearEvents()` to empty the list\n   - Closes `EventSource` on unmount\n\n2. **Create `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx`** — React client component that:\n   - Calls `useLiveFeed()`\n   - Renders connection status indicator (green/red dot + text)\n   - Renders Pause/Resume toggle button and Clear button in a toolbar\n   - Renders each event as a card/list item with: relative timestamp, event name colored chip, resolved identity (IdentityChip), properties (JsonChip)\n   - Handles empty state (\"No events yet\")\n\n3. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts`** — unit tests for the hook\n\n4. **Create `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx`** — unit tests for the component\n\n5. **Modify `src/app/test/page.tsx`** — import `LiveFeed` and replace the placeholder `<Paper>` content in the right panel\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n- [ ] Linter → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/useLiveFeed.ts` exists and exports `useLiveFeed`\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/LiveFeed.tsx` exists and exports `LiveFeed`\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts` exists\n- [ ] File `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx` exists\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Live` (connection status text)\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Pause` (pause/resume button)\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/test` contains `Clear` (clear button)\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/useLiveFeed.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `useLiveFeed` from `@/components/test/useLiveFeed`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Initial state: events array is empty, status is `\"disconnected\"`, paused is `false`\n  - Receiving SSE messages prepends events to the list (newest first)\n  - Events list is capped at 200; when a 201st event arrives the oldest is dropped\n  - `togglePause()` sets paused to `true`; incoming events during pause are buffered\n  - Resuming (calling `togglePause()` again) flushes buffered events into state\n  - `clearEvents()` resets the events array to empty\n  - Connection status transitions to `\"live\"` when EventSource opens\n  - Connection status transitions to `\"disconnected\"` when EventSource fires error\n  - EventSource is closed on unmount (cleanup)\n\n- **Test file**: `src/components/test/__tests__/LiveFeed.test.tsx`\n- **Module under test**: `LiveFeed` from `@/components/test/LiveFeed`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Renders connection status indicator with text \"Live\" or \"Disconnected\"\n  - Renders Pause and Clear buttons\n  - Shows empty state text when no events\n  - Renders event cards with event name, relative timestamp, resolved identity, and properties when events exist\n  - Clicking Pause toggles to Resume label\n  - Clicking Clear empties the event list\n\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\nNone. The SSE endpoint (`GET /api/live`) is already implemented in F17. The spec is clear on all UI behaviors. Relative timestamps (e.g., \"2s ago\") will be computed client-side; no external dependency is needed — a simple `formatRelativeTime` helper suffices.\n","numLines":110,"startLine":1,"totalLines":110}}}
