{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019ADSTrsFgDT4eZhqbKNvkS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\n4\timport Button from \"@mui/material/Button\";\n5\timport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\n6\timport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\n7\timport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n8\timport { useState } from \"react\";\n9\timport type {\n10\t  EventPayload,\n11\t  SendResult,\n12\t} from \"@/components/test/useEventSender\";\n13\t\n14\t// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n15\t\n16\tinterface CustomEventFormProps {\n17\t  sendEvent: (payload: EventPayload) => Promise<SendResult>;\n18\t}\n19\t\n20\t// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n21\t\n22\texport function CustomEventForm({\n23\t  sendEvent,\n24\t}: CustomEventFormProps): React.JSX.Element {\n25\t  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);\n26\t\n27\t  // Form field state\n28\t  const [eventName, setEventName] = useState(\"\");\n29\t  const [deviceId, setDeviceId] = useState(\"\");\n30\t  const [userId, setUserId] = useState(\"\");\n31\t  const [timestamp, setTimestamp] = useState(\"\");\n32\t  const [propertiesRaw, setPropertiesRaw] = useState(\"\");\n33\t  const [propertiesError, setPropertiesError] = useState(false);\n34\t\n35\t  // Submit feedback\n36\t  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n37\t  const [feedback, setFeedback] = useState<{\n38\t    type: \"success\" | \"error\";\n39\t    message: string;\n40\t  } | null>(null);\n41\t\n42\t  function handlePropertiesChange(raw: string): void {\n43\t    setPropertiesRaw(raw);\n44\t    if (raw.trim() === \"\") {\n45\t      setPropertiesError(false);\n46\t      return;\n47\t    }\n48\t    try {\n49\t      JSON.parse(raw);\n50\t      setPropertiesError(false);\n51\t    } catch {\n52\t      setPropertiesError(true);\n53\t    }\n54\t  }\n55\t\n56\t  async function handleSubmit(e: React.FormEvent): Promise<void> {\n57\t    e.preventDefault();\n58\t    if (!eventName.trim() || propertiesError) return;\n59\t\n60\t    const payload: EventPayload = { event_name: eventName.trim() };\n61\t    if (deviceId.trim()) payload.device_id = deviceId.trim();\n62\t    if (userId.trim()) payload.user_id = userId.trim();\n63\t    if (timestamp.trim()) payload.timestamp = timestamp.trim();\n64\t    if (propertiesRaw.trim()) {\n65\t      try {\n66\t        payload.properties = JSON.parse(propertiesRaw) as Record<\n67\t          string,\n68\t          unknown\n69\t        >;\n70\t      } catch {\n71\t        setPropertiesError(true);\n72\t        return;\n73\t      }\n74\t    }\n75\t\n76\t    setLoading(true);\n77\t    setFeedback(null);\n78\t    const result = await sendEvent(payload);\n79\t    setLoading(false);\n80\t    setFeedback(\n81\t      result.success\n82\t        ? { type: \"success\", message: \"Sent\" }\n83\t        : { type: \"error\", message: result.error ?? \"Error\" },\n84\t    );\n85\t  }\n86\t\n87\t  return (\n88\t    <Box data-testid=\"custom-event-form\">\n89\t      <Button\n90\t        variant=\"outlined\"\n91\t        size=\"small\"\n92\t        onClick={() => setOpen((v) => !v)}\n93\t        fullWidth\n94\t      >\n95\t        Custom Event\n96\t      </Button>\n97\t\n98\t      {open && (\n99\t        <Box\n100\t          component=\"form\"\n101\t          onSubmit={(e) => void handleSubmit(e)}\n102\t          sx={{ mt: 1 }}\n103\t        >\n104\t          <Stack spacing={1}>\n105\t            <TextField\n106\t              label=\"Event Name\"\n107\t              value={eventName}\n108\t              onChange={(e) => setEventName(e.target.value)}\n109\t              size=\"small\"\n110\t              required\n111\t              fullWidth\n112\t            />\n113\t            <TextField\n114\t              label=\"Device ID\"\n115\t              value={deviceId}\n116\t              onChange={(e) => setDeviceId(e.target.value)}\n117\t              size=\"small\"\n118\t              fullWidth\n119\t            />\n120\t            <TextField\n121\t              label=\"User ID\"\n122\t              value={userId}\n123\t              onChange={(e) => setUserId(e.target.value)}\n124\t              size=\"small\"\n125\t              fullWidth\n126\t            />\n127\t            <TextField\n128\t              label=\"Timestamp\"\n129\t              type=\"datetime-local\"\n130\t              value={timestamp}\n131\t              onChange={(e) => setTimestamp(e.target.value)}\n132\t              size=\"small\"\n133\t              fullWidth\n134\t              slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n135\t            />\n136\t            <TextField\n137\t              label=\"Properties\"\n138\t              value={propertiesRaw}\n139\t              onChange={(e) => handlePropertiesChange(e.target.value)}\n140\t              size=\"small\"\n141\t              multiline\n142\t              rows={3}\n143\t              fullWidth\n144\t              error={propertiesError}\n145\t              helperText={propertiesError ? \"Invalid JSON\" : undefined}\n146\t              placeholder='{\"key\": \"value\"}'\n147\t              slotProps={{ htmlInput: { style: { fontFamily: \"monospace\" } } }}\n148\t            />\n149\t\n150\t            <Button\n151\t              type=\"submit\"\n152\t              variant=\"contained\"\n153\t              size=\"small\"\n154\t              disabled={!eventName.trim() || propertiesError || loading}\n155\t              fullWidth\n156\t            >\n157\t              Send\n158\t            </Button>\n159\t\n160\t            {feedback != null && (\n161\t              <Typography\n162\t                variant=\"caption\"\n163\t                color={\n164\t                  feedback.type === \"success\" ? \"success.main\" : \"error.main\"\n165\t                }\n166\t              >\n167\t                {feedback.type === \"success\"\n168\t                  ? \"Sent\"\n169\t                  : `Error: ${feedback.message}`}\n170\t              </Typography>\n171\t            )}\n172\t          </Stack>\n173\t        </Box>\n174\t      )}\n175\t    </Box>\n176\t  );\n177\t}\n178\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"496fb2ae-93e4-48b2-b968-7ed4da55eb0e","uuid":"0e77a3dd-c995-4200-850e-d4cee51b8b3f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:04:22.947Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Button from \"@mui/material/Button\";\nimport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\nimport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\nimport { useState } from \"react\";\nimport type {\n  EventPayload,\n  SendResult,\n} from \"@/components/test/useEventSender\";\n\n// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface CustomEventFormProps {\n  sendEvent: (payload: EventPayload) => Promise<SendResult>;\n}\n\n// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function CustomEventForm({\n  sendEvent,\n}: CustomEventFormProps): React.JSX.Element {\n  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);\n\n  // Form field state\n  const [eventName, setEventName] = useState(\"\");\n  const [deviceId, setDeviceId] = useState(\"\");\n  const [userId, setUserId] = useState(\"\");\n  const [timestamp, setTimestamp] = useState(\"\");\n  const [propertiesRaw, setPropertiesRaw] = useState(\"\");\n  const [propertiesError, setPropertiesError] = useState(false);\n\n  // Submit feedback\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n  const [feedback, setFeedback] = useState<{\n    type: \"success\" | \"error\";\n    message: string;\n  } | null>(null);\n\n  function handlePropertiesChange(raw: string): void {\n    setPropertiesRaw(raw);\n    if (raw.trim() === \"\") {\n      setPropertiesError(false);\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      JSON.parse(raw);\n      setPropertiesError(false);\n    } catch {\n      setPropertiesError(true);\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function handleSubmit(e: React.FormEvent): Promise<void> {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!eventName.trim() || propertiesError) return;\n\n    const payload: EventPayload = { event_name: eventName.trim() };\n    if (deviceId.trim()) payload.device_id = deviceId.trim();\n    if (userId.trim()) payload.user_id = userId.trim();\n    if (timestamp.trim()) payload.timestamp = timestamp.trim();\n    if (propertiesRaw.trim()) {\n      try {\n        payload.properties = JSON.parse(propertiesRaw) as Record<\n          string,\n          unknown\n        >;\n      } catch {\n        setPropertiesError(true);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    setLoading(true);\n    setFeedback(null);\n    const result = await sendEvent(payload);\n    setLoading(false);\n    setFeedback(\n      result.success\n        ? { type: \"success\", message: \"Sent\" }\n        : { type: \"error\", message: result.error ?? \"Error\" },\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Box data-testid=\"custom-event-form\">\n      <Button\n        variant=\"outlined\"\n        size=\"small\"\n        onClick={() => setOpen((v) => !v)}\n        fullWidth\n      >\n        Custom Event\n      </Button>\n\n      {open && (\n        <Box\n          component=\"form\"\n          onSubmit={(e) => void handleSubmit(e)}\n          sx={{ mt: 1 }}\n        >\n          <Stack spacing={1}>\n            <TextField\n              label=\"Event Name\"\n              value={eventName}\n              onChange={(e) => setEventName(e.target.value)}\n              size=\"small\"\n              required\n              fullWidth\n            />\n            <TextField\n              label=\"Device ID\"\n              value={deviceId}\n              onChange={(e) => setDeviceId(e.target.value)}\n              size=\"small\"\n              fullWidth\n            />\n            <TextField\n              label=\"User ID\"\n              value={userId}\n              onChange={(e) => setUserId(e.target.value)}\n              size=\"small\"\n              fullWidth\n            />\n            <TextField\n              label=\"Timestamp\"\n              type=\"datetime-local\"\n              value={timestamp}\n              onChange={(e) => setTimestamp(e.target.value)}\n              size=\"small\"\n              fullWidth\n              slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n            />\n            <TextField\n              label=\"Properties\"\n              value={propertiesRaw}\n              onChange={(e) => handlePropertiesChange(e.target.value)}\n              size=\"small\"\n              multiline\n              rows={3}\n              fullWidth\n              error={propertiesError}\n              helperText={propertiesError ? \"Invalid JSON\" : undefined}\n              placeholder='{\"key\": \"value\"}'\n              slotProps={{ htmlInput: { style: { fontFamily: \"monospace\" } } }}\n            />\n\n            <Button\n              type=\"submit\"\n              variant=\"contained\"\n              size=\"small\"\n              disabled={!eventName.trim() || propertiesError || loading}\n              fullWidth\n            >\n              Send\n            </Button>\n\n            {feedback != null && (\n              <Typography\n                variant=\"caption\"\n                color={\n                  feedback.type === \"success\" ? \"success.main\" : \"error.main\"\n                }\n              >\n                {feedback.type === \"success\"\n                  ? \"Sent\"\n                  : `Error: ${feedback.message}`}\n              </Typography>\n            )}\n          </Stack>\n        </Box>\n      )}\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n","numLines":178,"startLine":1,"totalLines":178}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KF72V8Eb2M5w8ToGQ5UY59","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the project. Let me write the code. I'll start with the test files, then the implementation.\n\nLet me plan the EventSource mock carefully. \n\nFor `useLiveFeed.test.ts`:\n- Need to mock `EventSource` as a global\n- The mock needs to allow tests to:\n  1. Get the created instance \n  2. Simulate `onopen` callback\n  3. Simulate `onmessage` with data\n  4. Simulate `onerror`\n  5. Verify that `close()` was called\n\nFor `LiveFeed.test.tsx`, I'll mock the entire `useLiveFeed` module so I can control what the hook returns using `vi.mock()`. Since there's no global test setup file in the vitest config, I'll need to set up the EventSource mock in each test file. Now I'm ready to start writing the test implementations.\n\nWriting test files... Setting up the mock...\n\nNow I'm moving on to the second test file where I need to mock the `useLiveFeed` hook at the module level, but I have to be careful about the import order since mocking needs to happen before the component imports. Finishing the mock setup...\n\nFor the `useLiveFeed` hook tests, I'll need to mock `EventSource` since the hook uses it directly, but in the component tests I can skip that since I'm mocking the entire hook. I should also remember to place the `@vitest-environment jsdom` directive at the very top of the test file, and I'm realizing the \"use client\" directive in the hook might create some complications I need to work through.\n\nNow for the actual implementation, the tricky part is handling pause and resume with event buffering. I need to use a ref to track the paused state so the `onmessage` handler doesn't close over stale values—that way when events arrive while paused, they go into a buffer, and when resuming I can flush everything to state. I'm realizing there's a potential race condition here — if `bufferRef.current` gets modified between when I call `setPaused` and when `setEvents` actually executes, I might be working with stale data. I should probably flush the buffer synchronously right after updating the paused state instead of relying on a separate state setter. I see the race condition now—when `paused` flips to false, the ref updates synchronously but the effect fires asynchronously, so new messages arriving in that gap go straight to state while buffered messages flush after, causing them to appear out of order. I'm realizing the race condition is actually a problem—buffered messages end up before messages that arrived during the re-render gap, which breaks ordering. Since this edge case is unlikely and the spec doesn't address it, I'll go with the more atomic approach of flushing the buffer directly inside the state updater rather than using an effect.\n\nImplementing the flush logic...\n\nNow I need to write a test that covers the core scenario: pausing after some messages arrive, buffering new ones while paused, then resuming to flush them back into state. The test should verify that after toggling pause twice, the buffered events actually make it into the state. I'm checking whether Next.js `Link` will cause test issues, and looking through the existing test setup to see if there's already a mock in place for it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5914,"cache_read_input_tokens":49680,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5914},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"496fb2ae-93e4-48b2-b968-7ed4da55eb0e","uuid":"8212ccce-1851-4053-850e-39f04c9f399b"}
