{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011cRL1rFzpvavkvEcwPiWAS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t// @vitest-environment jsdom\n2\timport {\n3\t  cleanup,\n4\t  fireEvent,\n5\t  render,\n6\t  screen,\n7\t  waitFor,\n8\t} from \"@testing-library/react\";\n9\timport { afterEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\n10\timport { CustomEventForm } from \"@/components/test/CustomEventForm\";\n11\timport type {\n12\t  EventPayload,\n13\t  SendResult,\n14\t} from \"@/components/test/useEventSender\";\n15\t\n16\t// ─── Setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n17\t\n18\tafterEach(() => {\n19\t  cleanup();\n20\t  vi.clearAllMocks();\n21\t});\n22\t\n23\t// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n24\t\n25\tfunction openForm() {\n26\t  const toggle = screen.getByRole(\"button\", { name: /custom event/i });\n27\t  fireEvent.click(toggle);\n28\t}\n29\t\n30\t// ─── Tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n31\t\n32\tdescribe(\"CustomEventForm\", () => {\n33\t  describe(\"container\", () => {\n34\t    it(\"renders data-testid='custom-event-form' container\", () => {\n35\t      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n36\t      expect(screen.getByTestId(\"custom-event-form\")).toBeTruthy();\n37\t    });\n38\t  });\n39\t\n40\t  describe(\"collapsible\", () => {\n41\t    it(\"form fields are not visible initially (collapsed)\", () => {\n42\t      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n43\t      expect(\n44\t        screen.queryByRole(\"textbox\", { name: /event.?name/i }),\n45\t      ).toBeNull();\n46\t    });\n47\t\n48\t    it(\"form fields become visible after toggling open\", () => {\n49\t      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n50\t      openForm();"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"496fb2ae-93e4-48b2-b968-7ed4da55eb0e","uuid":"d5fa66bd-d089-4a3d-84ce-ef30d9bccff5","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:05:17.976Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx","content":"// @vitest-environment jsdom\nimport {\n  cleanup,\n  fireEvent,\n  render,\n  screen,\n  waitFor,\n} from \"@testing-library/react\";\nimport { afterEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\nimport { CustomEventForm } from \"@/components/test/CustomEventForm\";\nimport type {\n  EventPayload,\n  SendResult,\n} from \"@/components/test/useEventSender\";\n\n// ─── Setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  cleanup();\n  vi.clearAllMocks();\n});\n\n// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction openForm() {\n  const toggle = screen.getByRole(\"button\", { name: /custom event/i });\n  fireEvent.click(toggle);\n}\n\n// ─── Tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndescribe(\"CustomEventForm\", () => {\n  describe(\"container\", () => {\n    it(\"renders data-testid='custom-event-form' container\", () => {\n      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n      expect(screen.getByTestId(\"custom-event-form\")).toBeTruthy();\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe(\"collapsible\", () => {\n    it(\"form fields are not visible initially (collapsed)\", () => {\n      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n      expect(\n        screen.queryByRole(\"textbox\", { name: /event.?name/i }),\n      ).toBeNull();\n    });\n\n    it(\"form fields become visible after toggling open\", () => {\n      render(<CustomEventForm sendEvent={vi.fn()} />);\n      openForm();","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":218}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EXEQLJ7J9bvYggoJbg3ziJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me proceed to implement everything.\n\nFirst, let me write the test files, then the implementation.\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n1. For `useLiveFeed.test.ts`: Mock `EventSource` as a global, use `renderHook` from React Testing Library\n2. For `LiveFeed.test.tsx`: Mock the `useLiveFeed` module entirely\n\n**Important consideration for LiveFeed.test.tsx**: Since `LiveFeed` will use `IdentityChip` (which uses Next.js `Link`), I need to either mock `next/link` or be careful. Let me check if any existing tests render components that use Next.js Link...\n\n\nLooking at the existing tests, none of them render components with Link. The `IdentityChip` component does use `next/link`, and in a vitest with jsdom environment, this could throw an error without proper router context. I'll need to mock the `next/link` module to provide a simple wrapper component that just renders the children with the href as an anchor element.\n\nNow I'm setting up the implementation plan and starting to write the code.\n\nWriting the hook implementation... Setting up error handling and cleanup for the connection, then implementing a pause toggle that buffers incoming events while paused and flushes them back into the state when resuming, along with a function to clear all events.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the TypeScript setup — `EventSource` should be available from the DOM library in the tsconfig, and I need to be careful about how `renderHook` handles the `useEffect` timing when setting up the mock event source for tests.\n\nWriting test file... Writing test cases... Writing the cap test...\n\nI realize batching all 200 event inserts into a single `act()` call will be much more efficient than calling it 201 times, which could cause timeouts. Now I'm moving on to write the togglePause test.\n\nWriting test cases... Writing test cases... Writing component tests...\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to handle the mocking strategy for the component tests. I need to mock `useLiveFeed` to control the hook's state, and I also need to handle `next/link` since `IdentityChip` depends on it. The simplest approach is to mock `useLiveFeed` entirely so I can return whatever state I need for each test case, and stub out `next/link` as a basic anchor tag to avoid import issues. Setting up test mocks... Setting up the mock with a factory function that returns the hook, then I'll configure each test to return specific values for the feed state like events, pause status, and connection indicators. Now I'm thinking through the test cases I need to cover: rendering the connection status, checking for the pause and clear buttons, and handling the empty state when there are no events.\n\nI also need to handle the event cards themselves, making sure they display the event name, timestamp, resolved identity, and properties. For the pause toggle test, I'll need to update the mock between renders to simulate the state change, since clicking the button calls `togglePause` but doesn't automatically update the `paused` value from the hook. I'm realizing the issue with this test approach—mocking the hook means the component won't actually re-render when the button is clicked, since `togglePause` is just a mock function that doesn't trigger any state changes. I should instead test that `togglePause` gets called when the button is clicked, rather than trying to verify the visual toggle without real hook state.\n\nA better strategy is to test the two states separately by mocking the hook with different return values—one render with `paused: false` to verify the \"Pause\" button appears, and another render with `paused: true` to verify the \"Resume\" button appears.\n\nWriting test cases... Still writing test assertions...\n\nNow I'm thinking through the test for rendering event cards—I need to set up the mock with some sample events and verify they display correctly on the component. Writing test assertions...\n\nNow I'm thinking through the LiveFeed component structure—it needs to display the connection status with a visual indicator, provide controls for pausing and clearing events, handle the empty state, and render each event as a card showing the timestamp, event name in a chip, and the resolved identity.\n\nFor the event name chips, I'll map event types to color variants deterministically rather than hardcoding specific colors. The `formatRelativeTime` helper will convert timestamps into readable relative time strings, and I'll implement it directly in the component file.\n\nSince `useLiveFeed.ts` uses the `\"use client\"` directive like `useEventSender.ts` does, the test setup should follow the same pattern without issues. Now I need to figure out what to import in the test files.\n\nI'll need to import the hook and component from their respective locations, along with the testing utilities. One thing I'm realizing is that when I write the tests first, they'll fail until the implementation exists, but I need to be careful about import errors—if a file doesn't exist yet, the test won't even load properly. I should structure the mocks carefully to avoid import failures before the actual code is written. I'm going to write the test files first, then create stub implementations, and finally fill in the actual logic—this way the tests can at least run and fail on assertions rather than import errors.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":710,"cache_read_input_tokens":59382,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":710},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"496fb2ae-93e4-48b2-b968-7ed4da55eb0e"